 be nil<br>&gt;&gt;&gt;                                // otherwise it returns the result of NOT operator.<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; This is also cannot work with Swift 2.1.<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; If the basic value operator can work with optional types, it will save multiple lines in out code.<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; Thanks!<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; Jiannan, Cao<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; _______________________________________________<br>&gt;&gt; swift-evolution mailing list<br>&gt;&gt; swift-evolution at swift.org &lt;mailto:swift-evolution at swift.org&gt;<br>&gt;&gt; https://lists.swift.org/mailman/listinfo/swift-evolution<br>&gt; <br></p><p><br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/attachments/20160216/306b4e33/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></div>    </main>
